<h2>Using ClipBoard-2000</h2>
ClipBoard is intended to be used in a wide variety of environments ranging from K-12 through higher-ed and corporate environments.  As such it is designed
to be intuitive and easy to use.  ClipBoard preoduces web-based lectures
using Quicktime technology from Apple Computer, Inc.
<p>
ClipBoard supports (at least) two basic modes of usage:
<ul>
<li><b>Lecture Replacement</b> - A lecture (often with video) is recorded
using ClipBoard with no audience present and viewed by students 
instead of attending the lecture.  This is the "distance education" 
scenario.  This is also useful when one wants to create a lecture archive in 
a particular topic such as the CERN Web Lecture Archive.
<li><b>Lecture Recording</b> - In this mode, ClipBoard is used to record 
(typically only the audio) a lecture while it is being given live.  This
lecture is then uploaded for the students to review and replay as part
of an entire learning process.  
</ul>
